---
// src/pages/saudi-red-sea-seafood-guide-2026.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Saudi Arabia Red Sea Seafood Guide 2026" 
  description="Explore Jeddah's fresh Red Sea seafood scene. Compare grilled hammour, lobster, and king prawns, and discover where to eat along the Corniche."
  canonicalUrl="https://www.sauditravelhub.com/saudi-red-sea-seafood-guide-2026/"
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [{
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the most popular fish in Jeddah?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Hammour (brown-spotted grouper) is the most famous and popular fish caught and eaten along the Saudi Red Sea coast, usually grilled or fried with local spices."
      }
    }, {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Where can tourists eat fresh seafood in Jeddah?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The Central Fish Market (Bangala) in Jeddah is the best place to buy fresh catch and have it cooked nearby. High-end dining options are available along the Jeddah Corniche."
      }
    }]
  }
  </script>

  <main id="main-content" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 7rem 1.5rem 3rem; font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--white);">
    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <header style="margin-bottom: 3rem; text-align: center;">
      <div style="font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--gold); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Cuisine &amp; Dining · Coastal Flavors</div>
      <h1 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.75rem; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff;">Saudi Red Sea Seafood Culinary Guide</h1>
      
      <div style="position: relative; border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; margin-top: 2rem; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
        <img 
          src="/images/saudi_red_sea_seafood.png" 
          alt="Fresh Red Sea seafood grilled on Jeddah Corniche" 
          loading="lazy"
          style="width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; max-height: 450px; object-fit: cover;" 
        />
        <div style="position: absolute; bottom: 0; left: 0; right: 0; background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(5,13,26,0.95) 0%, rgba(5,13,26,0.5) 60%, transparent 100%); padding: 1.5rem 2rem; text-align: left;">
          <p style="color: var(--white); font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0; font-style: italic; font-weight: 500; text-shadow: 1px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.95);">Grilled hammour, lobster and king prawns caught fresh from some of the world's richest marine waters.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- TABS NAVIGATION -->
    <div class="tabs-nav" style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 2rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="guide" style="background: none; border: none; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--gold); padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; color: #fff; font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.3s ease;">Seafood Guide</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="background" style="background: none; border: none; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; color: var(--white-dim); font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.3s ease;">Background &amp; Origin</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="recent" style="background: none; border: none; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; color: var(--white-dim); font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.3s ease;">Recent Blogs</button>
    </div>

    <!-- TABS CONTENT -->
    <div class="tab-content" id="tab-guide" style="display: block;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700;">Essential Red Sea Seafood Varieties</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Due to its high salinity and warm temperatures, the Red Sea is home to incredibly sweet, flavorful fish and shellfish. When dining at seafood restaurants in Jeddah or Yanbu, look for these local favorites:</p>
      
      <div style="background: var(--surface2); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <h4 style="color: var(--gold); font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700;">Seafood Dining Stats</h4>
        <ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; font-size: 1rem;">
          <li>🐟 <strong>Most Famous Fish:</strong> Hammour (Red Sea Grouper)</li>
          <li>🦞 <strong>Premium Shellfish:</strong> Red Sea Spiny Lobster</li>
          <li>🍤 <strong>Local Favorite:</strong> Jambo Prawns (King Prawns)</li>
          <li>🔥 <strong>Best Cook Method:</strong> Grilled with olive oil, cumin, and garlic</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">The 3 Must-Try Seafood Dishes</h3>
      <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; list-style-type: square; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
        <li><strong>1. Sayadiyah Rice &amp; Fish:</strong> The ultimate coastal specialty. Fish (usually Najil or Hammour) is fried and served over rice that has been cooked in a rich, dark broth flavored with deeply caramelized onions, cumin, and spices. It has a beautiful brown color and a sweet-savory flavor.</li>
        <li><strong>2. Spiced Grilled Najil:</strong> Najil (Saddleback Grouper) is considered the most premium and expensive fish in the Red Sea. Its flesh is pearly white, firm, and naturally sweet. It is typically cut open flat, rubbed with a mixture of garlic, cumin, coriander, and lemon juice, and grilled over hot coals.</li>
        <li><strong>3. Fried Red Sea Prawns:</strong> Huge king prawns marinated in local spices, coated in flour, and deep-fried until crispy. They are always served with hot garlic dipping sauce (toum) and fresh Arabic flatbread.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="tab-content" id="tab-background" style="display: none;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700;">Jeddah's Sayadiyah &amp; Seafood Traditions</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">While Najd is famous for slow-cooked meat, the western Hijaz coast has always looked to the sea. The culinary history of Jeddah, Yanbu, and Umluj is defined by the daily catch brought in by local fishermen.</p>
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"><strong>The Central Fish Market (Bangala):</strong> To truly experience Jeddah's seafood culture, tourists must visit the Central Fish Market near Al-Balad. Here, hundreds of local fishermen auction off fresh hammour, najil, red snapper, prawns, and crabs every morning. You can buy your fish directly, take it to the cleaning section, and have it immediately cooked at the adjacent traditional grilling stalls.</p>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;"><strong>Traditional Spices:</strong> Red Sea cooking differs from inland Saudi cuisine. Instead of heavy spices like cinnamon and saffron, coastal chefs rely on fresh garlic, green chilies, cumin, coriander, and fresh lemon juice. This preserves the delicate, sweet flavor of the fresh catch. Sayadiyah rice is the signature dish of this coastal identity, representing the connection between Jeddah's trading heritage and the Red Sea.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tab-content" id="tab-recent" style="display: none;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700;">Explore More Saudi Food Guides</h2>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
        <a href="/saudi-arabia-traditional-food-guide-15-dishes" style="display: block; padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; background: var(--surface2); color: #fff; text-decoration: none; transition: border-color 0.3s ease;">
          <strong style="color: var(--gold); display: block; font-size: 1.1rem;">📖 15 Traditional Saudi Dishes &rarr;</strong>
          <span style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--white-dim);">Compare all the major rice, meat, street food, and dessert options in the Kingdom.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/saudi-mutabbaq-recipe-street-food-2026" style="display: block; padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; background: var(--surface2); color: #fff; text-decoration: none; transition: border-color 0.3s ease;">
          <strong style="color: var(--gold); display: block; font-size: 1.1rem;">🥞 Authentic Saudi Mutabbaq Recipe &rarr;</strong>
          <span style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--white-dim);">Learn to make Jeddah's favorite crispy, stuffed pan-fried street food flatbread.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/best-areas-to-stay-in-jeddah-tourists-2026" style="display: block; padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; background: var(--surface2); color: #fff; text-decoration: none; transition: border-color 0.3s ease;">
          <strong style="color: var(--gold); display: block; font-size: 1.1rem;">🏨 Best Areas to Stay in Jeddah &rarr;</strong>
          <span style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--white-dim);">Plan where to stay along the Corniche or historic Al-Balad.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <script slot="body">
    const buttons = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn');
    const contents = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content');
    buttons.forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        buttons.forEach(b => {
          b.classList.remove('active');
          b.style.borderBottomColor = 'transparent';
          b.style.color = 'var(--white-dim)';
        });
        contents.forEach(c => c.style.display = 'none');
        btn.classList.add('active');
        btn.style.borderBottomColor = 'var(--gold)';
        btn.style.color = '#fff';
        const target = document.getElementById(`tab-${btn.dataset.tab}`);
        target.style.display = 'block';
      });
    });
  </script>
</Layout>

<style>
  .tab-btn.active {
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--gold) !important;
    color: #fff !important;
  }
</style>
